div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe flex-start; justify-content: unsafe center; width: 398px; height: 1px; padding-top: 7px; margin-left: 101px;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #000000; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

font.font: A client books an initial appointment with a practitioner. Client advised that they will receive a request to complete a questionnaire online.

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe flex-start; justify-content: unsafe center; width: 398px; height: 1px; padding-top: 87px; margin-left: 101px;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #000000; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

font.font: At the time of booking, the member of staff who recorded the appointment can enter the CIMS, create a new file for the client and generate what in OMSSS is called a 'collection'.

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe flex-start; justify-content: unsafe center; width: 398px; height: 1px; padding-top: 167px; margin-left: 101px;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #000000; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

font.font: The CIMS will use the OMSSS API to request a new collection.

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe flex-start; justify-content: unsafe center; width: 398px; height: 1px; padding-top: 247px; margin-left: 101px;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #000000; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

font.font: The OMSSS will send a link or QR code to the client, identifying the health practitioner/service provider organisation as the source. When the client follows the link they will be taken to the measure for them to fill in.

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe flex-start; justify-content: unsafe center; width: 398px; height: 1px; padding-top: 347px; margin-left: 101px;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #000000; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

font.font: The client completes the measure either at home on their own device or in the waiting room prior to their appointment.

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe flex-start; justify-content: unsafe center; width: 398px; height: 1px; padding-top: 427px; margin-left: 101px;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #000000; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

font.b: Completed measure is uploaded in other systems

font.font: When the client completes the measure in OMSSS, the original CIMS will be notified and can request the individual item scores for storage in its database. OMSSS can optionally email a report of the results to the psychologist. The report does not include personal client details. The email will include a code that the psychologist can use to match to their client records.
